# HarborOps Inventory Module Expansion — Implementation Plan

## Architectural Overview

The auth module is the canonical pattern: `schema.ts` (Zod) → `service.ts` (class singleton, all Prisma calls) → `controller.ts` (thin handlers, parse → call service → respond) → `routes.ts` (wire middleware + controller). The inventory module currently has everything inline in `routes.ts`. The task is to extract into this pattern, add new endpoints, update the scheduler, and write tests.

The global `errorHandler` already handles `ZodError` (400), Prisma P2002 (409), Prisma P2025 (404). Business-level errors use the same `throw Object.assign(new Error(...), { statusCode, code })` pattern from `auth.service.ts`. All handlers use `next(err)` — never `res.status(500)` directly.

---

## File 1: `backend/src/modules/inventory/inventory.schema.ts`

This file exports every Zod schema plus its inferred TypeScript type. Group by domain section with a comment banner.

```
