## Implementation Sequence

Execute in this order to avoid dependency failures:

1. **`inventory.schema.ts`** — No dependencies, creates the type contract everything else uses.
2. **`inventory.service.ts`** — Depends on schema types, prisma, config, encryption, exporter libs. Write all methods with their full business logic.
3. **`inventory.controller.ts`** — Depends on service and schema. Thin wrappers only.
4. **`inventory.routes.ts`** — Depends on controller. Replace file entirely.
5. **`scheduler.ts`** — Replace placeholder job body; add new job. Depends on prisma.
6. **`unit_tests/inventory.test.ts`** — Pure logic, no dependencies on service. Write and verify.
7. **`API_tests/inventory.test.ts`** — Integration tests, requires running server.

